typeProperties.script:
source(output(
		Empid as string,
		Name as string,
		Country as string,
		Department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 aggregate(groupBy(Department),
	Employeecount = count(Empid)) ~> Aggregate1
Aggregate1 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	input(
		{30} as string,
		Rahul as string,
		India as string,
		{33} as string
	),
	partitionFileNames:['aggregatefile.csv'],
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> sink1

source(output(
		Column_1 as string,
		Column_2 as string,
		Column_3 as integer '000',
		Column_4 as string,
		Column_5 as integer '000'
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source22
source(output(
		Column_1 as string,
		Column_2 as string,
		Column_3 as string,
		Column_4 as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source2
source22 aggregate(Column_3 = sum(Column_3),
		Column_5 = count(Column_5)) ~> Aggregate1
source22, Aggregate1 union(byName: true,
	partitionBy('roundRobin', 2))~> Union1
Union1 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1

source(output(
		empid as string,
		name as string,
		country as string,
		department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 filter(equals(department, '3')) ~> Filter1
Filter1 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	input(
		Column_1 as string,
		Column_2 as string,
		Column_3 as string,
		Column_4 as string,
		Column_5 as string
	),
	partitionFileNames:['filter.csv'],
	truncate: true,
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> sink1

source(output(
		Empid as string,
		Name as string,
		Country as string,
		Department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> Employeesdata
Employeesdata split(equals(Department, '1'),
	equals(Department, '2'),
	equals(Department, '3'),
	disjoint: false) ~> ConditionalSplit1@(ITEmployees, HREmployees, PayrollEmployees, OtherEmployees)
ConditionalSplit1@ITEmployees sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	input(
		{30} as string,
		Rahul as string,
		India as string,
		{33} as string
	),
	partitionFileNames:['conditiona.csv'],
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> sink1
ConditionalSplit1@HREmployees sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	input(
		{30} as string,
		Rahul as string,
		India as string,
		{33} as string
	),
	partitionFileNames:['hremployees.csv'],
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> sink2

source(output(
		EmplName as string,
		EmplDept as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: true,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 split(isNull(EmplName),
	disjoint: false) ~> ConditionalSplit1@(errorfolderoutput, outputfolder)
ConditionalSplit1@errorfolderoutput sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	truncate: true,
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> sink1
ConditionalSplit1@outputfolder sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	truncate: true,
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1)) ~> sink2

source(output(
		Empid as string,
		Name as string,
		Country as string,
		Department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 split(equals(Department, '1'),
	equals(Department, '2'),
	equals(Department, '3'),
	disjoint: false) ~> ConditionalSplit1@(ITemployees, HREmployees, PayrollEmployees, Others)
ConditionalSplit1@ITemployees sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,

		Department as string,
		Employeecount as string
	),

ConditionalSplit1@HREmployees sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,

	),

ConditionalSplit1@PayrollEmployees sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	input(
		Department as string,

	),
	partitionFileNames:['harishpayrollempl.csv'],

ConditionalSplit1@Others sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,

	),

source(output(
		id as string,
		os_version as string,
		model as string,
		app_version as string,
		os_type as string,
		udid as string,
		imei as string,
		serial_number as string,
		hardware_serial_number as string,
		name as string,
		product_name as string,
		activated_at as string,
		last_app_connection as string,
		user as (id as string, name as string, email as string, external_id as string, organization as (name as string, id as string)),
		identifier as string,
		health_status as string,
		compliance_status as string,
		risk_status as string,
		mdm_status as string,
		current_health_warnings as string[],
		current_compliance_warnings as string[],
		current_risk_warnings as string[],
		compromised as boolean,
		configuration as (location_services as string, push_notifications as string, personal_vpn as string, default_installer as string, system_admin as string, samsung_knox_services as string),
		stats as (networks_monitored as string, access_points_scanned as string, apps_analyzed as string, incidents as (network as (open as string, total as string), malware as (open as string, total as string), indicator_of_compromise as (open as string, total as string), configuration as (open as string, total as string), os as (open as string, total as string))),
		mdm as (username as string, device_id as string, friendly_name as string, last_connection as string, organization_group as string),
		container as boolean
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	limit: 100,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false,
	documentForm: 'arrayOfDocuments') ~> source1
source1 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1
